{{Expand German|Carl Patsch|date=August 2013}} {{Expand Polish|Karl Patsch|date=April 2012}} '''Carl Ludwig Patsch''', also '''Karl Ludwig Patsch''', {{lang-bg|'''Карл Пач'''}} (14 September 1865 in [[Kowatsch]] ({{lang-cs|[[Kovač (Jičín District)|Kovač]]}}) bei [[Jitschin]] {{ndash}} 21 February 1945 in [[Vienna]]) was an [[Austria]]n [[Slavist]], [[Albanologist]], archaeologist and historian.
Carl Patsch was born in north-east [[Bohemia]], as a son of Ludwig Patsch, a [[steward (office)|steward]] of an upper prince, but grew up in [[Maratschowka]] ({{lang-pl|[[Maraczówka]], Moraczówka}}, {{lang-uk|{{Interlanguage link multi|Марачівка|uk|3=Marachivka|lt=Maračivka}}}}) and [[Sławuta]] ({{lang-uk|[[Slavuta|Slavúta]]}}), [[Volhynia]]. He spoke Czech, Polish and Russian as mother languages.
