'''Frank Broeze''' (18 August 1945 – 4 April 2001) was a Professor of History at the [[University of Western Australia]].<ref>{{Citation | title=Broeze, Frank | journal=Trove | publication-date=2008 | url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.party-572071 }}</ref> His special area of interest was [[maritime history]].

==Life and work==

Born '''Franklin Jan Aart Broeze''' in [[Rijswijk]], [[Netherlands]], Broeze was a maritime historian, and was one of the founders of the [[Australian Association for Maritime History]]. He published widely on maritime history issues<ref>{{Citation | author1=Broeze, Frank | title=Mr Brooks and the Australian trade : imperial business in the nineteenth century | publication-date=1993 | publisher=Melbourne University Press | isbn=978-0-522-84574-7 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation | author1=Broeze, Frank | author2=Henderson, Graeme, 1947- | author3=Western Australian Museum | author4=Broeze, Frank J. A | author5=Henderson, Graeme | title=Western Australians & the sea : our maritime heritage | publication-date=1986 | publisher=Western Australian Museum | isbn=978-0-7309-1244-6 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation | author1=Broeze, Frank | title=Island nation : a history of Australians and the sea | publication-date=1998 | publisher=St. Leonards, N.S.W. Allen & Unwin | isbn=978-1-74269-668-3 }}</ref> as well as editing.<ref>{{Citation | author1=Broeze, Frank | title=Brides of the sea : port cities of Asia from the 16th-20th centuries | publication-date=1989 | publisher=New South Wales University Press | isbn=978-0-86840-203-1 }}</ref> He wrote ten books and had more than 100 articles published in academic journals.<ref>Obituary by Michael Pearson, [http://www.humanities.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/AAH-Obit-Broeze-2001.pdf ''Australian Academy of the Humanities, Proceedings'', 26, 2001]</ref>

Broeze died on 4 April 2001 in [[Perth]], [[Western Australia]].<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1111/1467-8446.00090 | volume=41 | title=Obituary: Franklin (Frank) Jan Aart Broeze, 1945-2001 | year=2001 | journal=Australian Economic History Review | pages=325–326 | author=Tull Malcolm}}</ref> The Frank Broeze Memorial Maritime History Book Prize was created by the [[Australian National Maritime Museum]] in his memory.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.anmm.gov.au/get-involved/grants-and-awards/history-prizes |title=History Prizes |publisher=[[Australian National Maritime Museum]] |accessdate=28 December 2015}}</ref> In addition,  a memorial lecture was inaugurated.<ref>{{Citation | author1=Beazley, Kim | author2=Australian Labor Party | title={{sic|Inau|gral|hide=y}} Frank Broeze Memorial Lecture | publication-date=2002-09-13 | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/192981311 | accessdate=10 December 2015 }}</ref>

