{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2012}} [[Image:Reghin13.JPG|thumb|right|Petru Maior]]
'''Petru Maior''' ({{IPA-ro|ˈpetru ˈmajor}}; 1761 in [[Târgu Mureș|Marosvásárhely]] ''(now Târgu Mureș, Romania)'' – 14 February 1821 in [[Budapest]]) was a [[Romanians|Romanian]] writer who is considered one of the most influential personalities of the [[Age of Enlightenment]] in [[Transylvania]] (the ''[[Transylvanian School]]''). Maior was a member of the [[Romanian Church United with Rome, Greek-Catholic|Greek-Catholic]] clergy, a historian, philosopher, and linguist.
The ''Buda Lexicon'', a book published in 1825, included two texts by Petru Maior, ''Orthographia romana sive latino-valachica una cum clavi'' and ''Dialogu pentru inceputul linbei române'', in which he introduced the letters ș for {{IPA|/ʃ/}} and ț for {{IPA|/ts/}}, which have since been in use in the [[Romanian alphabet]].<ref>Marinella Lörinczi Angioni, "Coscienza nazionale romanza e ortografia: il romeno tra alfabeto cirillico e alfabeto latino ", ''La Ricerca Folklorica'', No. 5, La scrittura: funzioni e ideologie. (Apr., 1982), pp. 75–85.</ref>
